Chima Azubuike, Gombe The Gombe State Government has procured modern firefighting equipment and facilities to strengthen the state fire service for effective response to emergencies. The materials include compound fumes used in fighting oil-related inferno, rescue lines, safety kits and uniforms, among others. Inaugurating the equipment on behalf of Governor Inuwa Yahaya on Saturday, the Commissioner for Special Duties, Mela Nunghe, said the procurement of the equipment was in fulfilment of the government’s commitment to safeguarding the lives and property of the citizens. Nunghe added that the state government was engaging the Federal Fire Service to procure more trucks so that they could reach all the 11 local government areas in the state. While commending the fire service officers for their diligence and sacrifice, the commissioner enjoined them to live up to expectation “as the government will continue to improve their working conditions and reward excellence.” He appealed to the people of the state to always cooperate with the officers and men of the fire service by promptly reporting fire incidents and disasters for action, adding that the state was now having “a first class firefighting equipment to tackle emergency incidents.” He warned the personnel of the fire service to ensure proper and effective use of the facilities, stressing that the abuse of the equipment would be punished. In his remarks, the Director, Gombe State Fire Service, Bakari Majidadi, lauded the Yahaya administration for equipping the service and gave an assurance that with such motivation, firefighting services would be taken to greater heights. ”Copyright PUNCH.
